==The Assembly==
===Talking to Lady Lovakengj===
* '''Councillor Unkar:''' ...and he says that it's of the greatest urgency.
* '''Lady Vulcana Lovakengj:''' Greatest urgency? I don't like urgency. This is quite simply not on.
* '''Player:''' Hiya!
* '''Lady Vulcana Lovakengj:''' Who is this human, Councillor Unkar? What are they doing here?
* {{tcond|If the player doees not have the requirements to start the quest:}}
** '''Councillor Unkar:''' I'm afraid I don't know.
** '''Lady Vulcana Lovakengj:''' Oh. Could you make them go away?
** '''Councillor Unkar:''' Sorry human. We're currently engaging in important official business. You'll need to come back another time.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has the requirements to start the quest:}}
** '''Councillor Unkar:''' This is [player name]. They've been helping out in Lovakengj recently.
** '''Lady Vulcana Lovakengj:''' Well I've never heard of them. What do they want?
** '''Councillor Unkar:''' What do you want human?
** Start The Forsaken Tower quest?
** {{topt|I'm looking for a quest.}}
*** '''Player:''' I'm looking for a quest.
*** '''Councillor Unkar:''' They're looking for a quest.
*** '''Lady Vulcana Lovakengj:''' A quest? Well we don't have any of those lying around.
*** '''Councillor Unkar:''' Well hang on. Maybe they could help us with this urgent matter.
*** '''Lady Vulcana Lovakengj:''' What urgent matter?
*** '''Councillor Unkar:''' The one we were just discussing. The one with the Doors of Dinh.
*** '''Lady Vulcana Lovakengj:''' Ah yes, the urgent matter with the Doors of Dinh. Very clever Councillor Unkar. You put the human to work. I need a sherry.
*** '''Lady Vulcana Lovakengj:''' Jorra! Bring me a sherry.
*** '''Jorra:''' Yes Lady Lovakengj.
*** '''Councillor Unkar:''' Human, we have a job for you.
*** '''Player:''' Great. What do you need?
*** '''Councillor Unkar:''' One of the finest smiths in Lovakengj, Undor, has been investigating issues with the Doors of Dinh. We've just received word that he has found the problem. However, he has requested we send assistance.
*** '''Councillor Unkar:''' Could you go to him and see what help he needs? You'll find him right outside the Doors of Dinh, north of Arceuus.
*** {{topt|Who are you?}}
**** '''Councillor Unkar:''' I'm Councillor Unkar, one of the members of the Kourend Council. We are responsible for running the entire Kingdom of Great Kourend.
**** '''Player:''' What brings you to Lovakengj then?
**** '''Councillor Unkar:''' It's important for the Council to maintain a good relationship with the rulers of the five cities. Although it is the Council that rules, we can only do so with their support.
**** '''Councillor Unkar:''' I'm here to help Lady Lovakengj out and to make sure she has everything she needs to rule effectively.
**** {{tact|other}}
*** {{topt|What are the Doors of Dinh?}}
**** '''Player:''' What are the Doors of Dinh?
**** '''Councillor Unkar:''' They are a great set of doors built by a legendary smith, Dinh, in the early days of Kourend. They were created to imprison a deadly beast known as the Wintertodt.
**** '''Councillor Unkar:''' Unfortunately, although the Doors kept the beast contained for over a thousand years, they've recently started to fail. The master smith, Undor, was sent to investigate.
**** {{tact|other}}
*** {{topt|I'll get going.}}
**** '''Player:''' I'll get going.
**** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|Nothing.}}
*** '''Player:''' Nothing.
*** '''Councillor Unkar:''' They don't want anything.
*** '''Lady Vulcana Lovakengj:''' Oh. Could you make them go away then?
*** '''Councillor Unkar:''' Sorry human. We're currently engaging in important official business. If you don't have anything of importance to say, you'll need to come back another time.
*** {{tact|end}}

