==The Quest for the Hammer==
===Talking to Undor before talking to Ignisia===
* '''Player:''' Hello.
* '''Undor:''' Well hello there [laddie/lassie].
* '''Player:''' I've been sent to help you.
* '''Undor:''' I just need to finish this little job. I'll be with you in a minute. While you're waiting, why not talk to that fiery lass? She'll fill you in on the situation here.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Undor after talking to Ignisia===
* '''Undor:''' Hello there [laddie/lass].
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Tell me about the Wintertodt.}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Tell me about the Doors of Dinh.}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Tell me about yourself.}}
* {{topt|I've been sent to help you.}}
** '''Player:''' I've been sent to help you.
** '''Undor:''' Have you now [laddie/lassie]? I was wondering when they'd send someone.
** '''Player:''' Well here I am. What do you need?
** '''Undor:''' They all kept saying that the Doors were failing and I kept telling them that was rubbish. Did they listen? Of course they didn't.
** '''Player:''' So the doors aren't failing?
** '''Undor:''' Of course not! They were made by Dinh himself, the finest smith this world has ever seen. His work doesn't just fail!
** '''Player:''' But if the Doors aren't failing, what's the issue?
** '''Undor:''' Sabotage!
** '''Player:''' Sabotage? That doesn't sound good.
** '''Undor:''' You're right with that one [laddie/lassie]. Someone or something has made a small hole in the Doors.
** '''Undor:''' It's not much, but it's enough for that Wintertodt to be able to draw some power into the prison. Probably why them fiery lot have had so much trouble recently.
** '''Player:''' So what do we do?
** '''Undor:''' Repair the damage of course [laddie/lassie]. Now I should be able to fix the issue no problem. The only thing I'm missing is the right tools. That's where you come in.
** '''Player:''' What tools do you need?
** '''Undor:''' I require a hammer!
** '''Player:''' A hammer? Are you seriously telling me that you don't own a hammer?
** '''Undor:''' What does it look like I'm holding you spoon?! I don't just need any hammer. I need the legendary hammer used by Dinh himself! It's the only tool capable of working this metal.
** '''Player:''' Ahh, I see. So where do I find this hammer?
** '''Undor:''' Back in his prime, Dinh built a great tower. It was known as Dinh's Redoubt and it's where he created all of his finest inventions.
** '''Undor:''' After Dinh died, some poncey mage thought they'd go and defile his tower. The place has been off limits ever since.
** '''Undor:''' Now I don't know for sure, but I reckon that Dinh's Hammer might still be there.
** '''Player:''' Well there's only one way to find out. Where do I find this tower?
** '''Undor:''' The Forsaken Tower, as it's now known, can be found west of Lovakengj.
** '''Player:''' Great, I'll be back once I've found that hammer.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Goodbye.}}

====Talking to Undor again====
* '''Undor:''' Hello there [laddie/lassie].
* {{topt|quest=No|Tell me about the Wintertodt.}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Tell me about the Doors of Dinh.}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Tell me about yourself.}}
* {{topt|Let's talk about my quest.}}
** '''Player:''' Let's talk about my quest.
** '''Undor:''' Have you got Dinh's Hammer yet [laddie/lassie]?
** '''Player:''' Not yet. Where should I be looking?
** '''Undor:''' I reckon it's somewhere in Dinh's Redoubt, or The Forsaken Tower, as it's now known. You'll find it west of Lovakengj.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Goodbye.}}

